  "featuredQuotes": [
    {
      "text": "My son is finishing fast to just play games like prodigy . He doesn’t work of handwriting at all!! Bring play back",
      "county": "Knox County District 6 Parent"
    },
    {
      "text": "My elementary children have repeatedly been exposed to inappropriate content on their school issued Chromebooks. They are often on websites that we do not allow at home. I am concerned how the screen time at school is affecting them academically.",
      "county": "Knox County District 4 Parent"
    },
    {
      "text": "I believe devices create a distraction and double the work for teachers.",
      "county": "Knox County District 4 Parent"
    },
    {
      "text": "Shows and movies being played without parents consent on screens very frequently.",
      "county": "Knox County District 4 Parent"
    },
    {
      "text": "I’d like to be able to access my child’s screen time per week and history",
      "county": "Knox County District 4 Parent"
    },
    {
      "text": "Screens seem to be used as a babysitter. My child in 4th grade did not get to play on the playground from Christmas break to the end of March because the teachers thought it was too cold and they had them sit inside on screens instead (not technically too cold to be outside per policy)",
      "county": "Knox County District 4 Parent"
    }
  ],
  "quotesByCounty": {
    "Knox County District 2 Parent": [
      {
        "text": "Excessive screen time reducing physical activity and face-to-face interaction\nPrivacy and data security concerns involving student information\nCyberbullying and inappropriate online behavior among students\nOverreliance on technology limiting development of critical thinking and handwriting skills\nExposure to inappropriate or unreliable online…",
        "county": "Knox County District 2 Parent"
      },
      {
        "text": "My biggest concern is that Chromebooks get used in place of peer interactions (like stations) Time where they can be working together independently but instead spend that time doing iready lessons.",
        "county": "Knox County District 2 Parent"
      }
    ],
    "Knox County District 4 Parent": [
      {
        "text": "There have been whisperings of Tcap testing being completely computerized next year. As a parent of a rising 3rd grader who struggles with test taking anxiety, my concern is that standardized testing on computers penalizes students for typing speed rather than content mastery.",
        "county": "Knox County District 4 Parent"
      },
      {
        "text": "The screens seem to be a band-aid for the help teachers have been needing since way before 2020. We just want more time with our amazing teachers or other wonderful personnel. And no more time with unnecessary games and videos that are not even allowed at our home.",
        "county": "Knox County District 4 Parent"
      },
      {
        "text": "Screen time was used for indoor recess, “brain breaks”, centers- virtually all day in different capacities. This includes shows/videos that the teacher would play. It was also an incentive for good behavior.",
        "county": "Knox County District 4 Parent"
      },
      {
        "text": "My children were both able to access the adult YouTube at school. We do not allow them to watch YouTube at home and monitor all screen use strictly. They also use Chromebooks for indoor recess and centers. There is also no communication about tv shows that are shown and how often- and tv shows were shown very frequently.",
        "county": "Knox County District 4 Parent"
      },
      {
        "text": "Screens seem to be used as a babysitter. My child in 4th grade did not get to play on the playground from Christmas break to the end of March because the teachers thought it was too cold and they had them sit inside on screens instead (not technically too cold to be outside per policy)",
        "county": "Knox County District 4 Parent"
      },
      {
        "text": "They are addictive, kids play non educational games on them all day. They cause too much distraction and do not add value.",
        "county": "Knox County District 4 Parent"
      }
    ],
    "Knox County District 5 Parent": [
      {
        "text": "Kids play academic games and rush through coursework to get to the reward. Spelling is atrocious when having to use pen and paper because teachers have them write essays on Google Docs so they turn on spellcheck and don’t pay attention to what actually needs to be fixed.",
        "county": "Knox County District 5 Parent"
      }
    ],
    "Knox County Parent": [
      {
        "text": "We are told from a young age that screen time hurts them. I was horrified when indound out my Kindergartener waa going to be given a screen. Why? \nIt take the content control from the parents. It is not what school should be about.",
        "county": "Knox County Parent"
      }
    ],
    "Knox County District 3 Parent": [
      {
        "text": "Screens create regression and lacks to diversify processing, it builds intolerance around patience and uncertainty.",
        "county": "Knox County District 3 Parent"
      }
    ],
    "Knox County District 6 Parent": [
      {
        "text": "My son is finishing fast to just play games like prodigy . He doesn’t work of handwriting at all!! Bring play back",
        "county": "Knox County District 6 Parent"
      }
